Peter Hess
CSC 242 - Project 4
April 2019

----------------------------

Linear Classifiers.

How to run: 

flags: 
	-f [filename] 
		Provide filename of example data (REQUIRED)

	-n [positive integer]
		Number of weight updates (optional - defaults to 10000)

	-a [double]
		value of alpha/step size (optional - defaults to _ with earthquake and _ with house data sets)

	-l
		uses logistic threshold (optional - default to hard threshold if not present)

	-d
		use decaying step size, decays at a rate of O(1/t), if present (optional)

----------------------------

Neural Networks

How to run: 

flags: 

	-f [filename] 
		Provide filename of example data (REQUIRED)

	-a [double]
		value of alpha/step size (optional - defaults to _ with earthquake and _ with house data sets)

	-l
		uses logistic threshold (optional - default to hard threshold if not present)

	-d
		use decaying step size, decays at a rate of O(1/t), if present (optional)